A_498 - The concept of the impossibility of lifting oneself by pulling oneself up by the shoelaces, described by Osho, but that only external people can intervene in certain circumstances to give help, as well as being precious in itself to make us understand that in certain circumstances it is impossible to make do, it is also valid for businesses and government and religious organizations. Generally, the more an opinion or information coming from outside is disinterested, honest and not contaminated by that particular person, company, organisation, the more it has value and is precious.